## 3. Game State Machine

The game is coordinated through a series of states. Transitions between states are managed entirely by the server and broadcasted to clients using packet `11` (`qa`) or `10` (`Ca`).

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> G_Lobby : Public Matchmaking
    [*] --> J_Lobby : Private Room
    
    G_Lobby --> K_Starting : 2+ Players Join
    J_Lobby --> K_Starting : Owner clicks Start!
    
    K_Starting --> F_RoundStart
    
    F_RoundStart --> V_WordSelection : Drawer chosen
    
    V_WordSelection --> j_Drawing : Drawer chooses word OR timer runs out
    
    j_Drawing --> Z_Reveal : Word guessed OR time runs out
    
    Z_Reveal --> V_WordSelection : Next drawer's turn
    Z_Reveal --> F_RoundStart : Next round begins
    Z_Reveal --> X_GameOver : All rounds complete
    
    X_GameOver --> J_Lobby : Back to Private Lobby
    X_GameOver --> G_Lobby : Back to Public Lobby
```

### State Enum Definitions (`L.id` / `e.id`)

| State Constant | Value | UI State Overlay | Action / Behavior |
| :--- | :---: | :--- | :--- |
| `G` | `0` | "Waiting for players..." | Shown when < 2 players are in a public lobby. |
| `K` | `1` | "Game starting in a few seconds..." | Countdown transition before game begins. |
| `F` | `2` | "Round X" | Round transition overlay (increments round). |
| `V` | `3` | Word Selection | Drawer selects a word. Others see "[Name] is choosing a word". |
| `j` | `4` | Active Gameplay | The drawer draws on the canvas; others type guesses in chat. |
| `Z` | `5` | Round Reveal | Shows correct word, round scores, and end reason. |
| `X` | `6` | Game Over | Shows podium leaderboard (1st, 2nd, 3rd) and winner. |
| `J` | `7` | Room Lobby | Private lobby waiting room. Allows configuring settings. |

