## 4. Socket.io Protocol Specification

The frontend connects via Socket.io and communicates primarily over two event channels:
1. `login`: Triggered on connection to initialize the player session.
2. `data`: Multiplexed gameplay events using a payload with `{ id: Number, data: Any }`.

### 4.1 Client-to-Server Events

#### Event: `login`
Sent by the client immediately after socket connection.
* **Payload**:
  ```json
  {
    "join": "roomId",      // Room code to join (string or 0)
    "create": 1,           // 1 if creating private room, 0 if public matchmaking
    "name": "PlayerName",  // Choosen name
    "lang": "0",           // Language index string
    "code": "",            // Optional secret token / hash
    "avatar": [0, 1, 2, -1] // [eyesIndex, mouthIndex, colorIndex, -1]
  }
  ```

#### Event: `data`
Multiplexed payload format: `{ id: Number, data: Any }`.

* **`id: 6` (Report Player)**:
  * Sent when a player reports another. Data: `{ id: targetPlayerId, reasons: Bitmask }` (toxic=1, spam=2, botting=4).
* **`id: 7` (Mute Player)**:
  * Sent when muting a player. Data: `targetPlayerId`.
* **`id: 8` (`Sa` - Rate Drawing)**:
  * Sent when rating the drawing. Data: `1` (like) or `0` (dislike).
* **`id: 9` (`ka` - Avatar Customization)**:
  * Sent when a player changes their avatar index in the lobby. Data: `avatarArray`.
* **`id: 12` (`xa` - Lobby Settings Update)**:
  * Sent when the lobby owner changes settings (Slots, Rounds, Drawtime, etc.). Data: `{ id: settingIndex, val: settingValue }`.
* **`id: 18` (`Aa` - Select Word)**:
  * Sent by the drawer when choosing a word. Data: `choiceIndex` (e.g. `0`, `1`, `2`) or `[choiceIndex1, choiceIndex2]` (in COMBINATION mode).
* **`id: 19` (`Ia` - Drawing commands)**:
  * Real-time canvas drawing data. Sent in batches of up to 8 drawing commands. Data: `[[type, color, size, x1, y1, x2, y2], ...]`.
* **`id: 20` (`Ra` - Clear Canvas)**:
  * Sent by drawer to clear the screen. No data field required.
* **`id: 21` (`Ta` - Undo/Sync Canvas Length)**:
  * Sent by drawer to undo the last stroke. Data: `newCommandsLength` (integer).
* **`id: 30` (`Na` - Chat Message / Guess)**:
  * Chat text guess. Data: `"my guess text"` (string).

---

### 4.2 Server-to-Client Events

#### Event: `joinerr`
If login fails, the server should emit `joinerr` with an error code:
* `1`: Room not found
* `2`: Room full
* `3`: You are on a kick cooldown
* `4`: You are banned from this room
* `5`: You are joining rooms too quickly
* `100`: You are already connected
* `200`: Too many users from your IP
* `300`: Kicked too many times

#### Event: `reason`
If a player gets disconnected due to an administrative action, the server should emit `reason` with:
* `1`: Kicked
* `2`: Banned

#### Event: `data`
The server multiplexes all game updates over this channel using `{ id: Number, data: Any }`.

* **`id: 1` (`ya` - Player Joined)**:
  * Broadcast to all players when a new user joins.
  * Data: Player Object:
    ```json
    {
      "id": 12,
      "flags": 0,             // bitwise flags (e.g., 4 represents ADMIN / Room Owner)
      "name": "Alex",
      "avatar": [0, 2, 4, -1],
      "score": 0,
      "guessed": false
    }
    ```
* **`id: 2` (`va` - Player Left)**:
  * Broadcast when a player leaves.
  * Data: `{ id: playerId, reason: 0_normal/1_kick/2_ban }`.
* **`id: 5` (`ba` - Kick Vote)**:
  * Broadcast when votekicking.
  * Data: `[voterId, targetId, currentVotes, requiredVotes]`.
* **`id: 8` (`Sa` - Rate Broadcast)**:
  * Broadcast a player's drawing rating.
  * Data: `{ id: playerId, vote: 0_dislike/1_like }`.
* **`id: 9` (`ka` - Avatar Sync)**:
  * Broadcast updated avatar.
  * Data: `{ id: playerId, avatar: avatarArray }`.
* **`id: 90` (`wa` - Name Sync)**:
  * Broadcast updated name.
  * Data: `{ id: playerId, name: newName }`.
* **`id: 10` (`Ca` - Lobby Initialization)**:
  * Sent directly to the client *only* upon successful login to load the game board.
  * Data payload structure:
    ```json
    {
      "me": 12,                // The client's unique player ID
      "type": 0,               // Room type (0 = public, 1 = private)
      "id": "abcde",           // Room ID (invite code)
      "settings": [0, 8, 80, 3, 3, 2, 0, 0], // Array of room setting values
      "users": [ ... ],        // Array of all Player Objects currently in the room
      "round": 0,              // Current round index (0-indexed)
      "owner": 12,             // Player ID of the room owner
      "state": {               // Active game state
        "id": 7,               // State Enum (e.g., 7 = private lobby)
        "time": 0,             // Remaining state timer
        "data": null           // Custom state data
      }
    }
    ```
* **`id: 11` (`qa` - Game State Transition)**:
  * Broadcast when the game transitions to a new phase.
  * Data: `{ id: StateEnum, time: seconds, data: StateCustomData }`.
    * For `F` (Round Transition): `data` is the round index (integer).
    * For `V` (Word Selection): `data` is `{ id: drawerId, words: ["apple", "banana", "cherry"] }` (words sent to drawer only; others receive `{ id: drawerId }`).
    * For `j` (Active Drawing): `data` is `{ id: drawerId, word: [lengthArray], drawCommands: [] }` (guessers receive length hints like `[5]` for apple; drawer receives the full string).
    * For `Z` (Reveal): `data` is `{ word: "apple", reason: 1_timeout/0_guessed, scores: [playerId, score, deltaScore, ...] }`.
    * For `X` (Game Over): `data` is list of rankings: `[[playerId, rankIndex, titleStr], ...]`.
* **`id: 12` (`xa` - Settings Broadcast)**:
  * Broadcast settings modifications.
  * Data: `{ id: settingIndex, val: settingValue }`.
* **`id: 14` (`La` - Timer Tick)**:
  * Broadcast every second.
  * Data: `timeRemaining` (integer).
* **`id: 15` (`Da` - Player Guessed Correctly)**:
  * Broadcast when a player guesses the word.
  * Data: `{ id: playerId, word: "guessed_word" }`.
* **`id: 16` (`$a` - Guess is Close)**:
  * Sent *only* to the client whose guess was close.
  * Data: `"GuesserName"` (string).
* **`id: 17` (`Ea` - Owner Change)**:
  * Broadcast when a new owner is appointed.
  * Data: `newOwnerPlayerId`.
* **`id: 19` (`Ia` - Drawing Stroke Sync)**:
  * Broadcast canvas stroke commands from drawer.
  * Data: `[[type, color, size, x1, y1, x2, y2], ...]`.
* **`id: 20` (`Ra` - Clear Canvas)**:
  * Broadcast clear canvas command. No data.
* **`id: 21` (`Ta` - Undo Stroke)**:
  * Broadcast stroke length removal.
  * Data: `newCommandsLength` (integer).
* **`id: 30` (`Na` - Chat Message Broadcast)**:
  * Broadcast chat messages.
  * Data: `{ id: senderPlayerId, msg: "text" }`.
* **`id: 31` (`Wa` - Warnings)**:
  * Broadcast system warning.
  * Data: `{ id: warningIndex, data: extraInfo }` (e.g. `{ id: 0 }` for "Need at least 2 players").

