## 5. Game Logic Mappings & Constants

### 5.1 Lobby Settings Index Array Mapping (`te` enum)
Lobby configurations are stored in an array matching these indices:
```javascript
const Settings = {
  LANG: 0,              // Language (0 = English, 1 = German, etc.)
  SLOTS: 1,             // Max players capacity (2-20)
  DRAWTIME: 2,          // Drawing time in seconds (15-240)
  ROUNDS: 3,            // Number of rounds (2-10)
  WORDCOUNT: 4,         // Number of word choices (1-5)
  HINTCOUNT: 5,         // Number of hints to show (0-5)
  WORDMODE: 6,          // Word mode (0 = Normal, 1 = Hidden, 2 = Combination)
  CUSTOMWORDSONLY: 7    // Use custom words only (0 = false, 1 = true)
}
```

### 5.2 Round End Reasons (`reason` in state `Z`)
* `0` (Everyone Guessed): Every active guesser guessed the word before time ran out.
* `1` (Time is Up): Timer expired.
* `2` (Drawer Left): The drawing player disconnected.
* `5` (Drawer Skipped): The drawer did not pick a word in time.

### 5.3 Player Admin Flags (`flags` field)
* `4`: Player is Lobby Owner (Admin). Shows a crown icon.

