## 9. Frontend Changes (UI Integration Points)

To accommodate the login requirements and premium monetization, the following adjustments must be implemented in the frontend assets:

### 9.1 Homepage "Unlock Premium" Button
* **Location**: Add a visually outstanding button in the home screen panels (e.g. next to the "Play" and "Create Private Room" buttons).
* **Identifier**: `button-unlock-premium`.
* **Behavior**:
  - If the user is already premium, the button says **"Premium Unlocked! ⭐"** and is disabled.
  - If not premium, clicking the button triggers the **Razorpay Checkout Modal** using the Razorpay JS SDK (`https://checkout.razorpay.com/v1/checkout.js`).

### 9.2 Game Board Color Panel Toggle
* **Location**: Rendered directly below the canvas toolbar (`#game-toolbar`).
* **UI Component**: A custom styled sliding switch:
  ```html
  <div class="color-panel-toggle-container">
      <span class="toggle-label">Enable Premium Colors</span>
      <label class="switch">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-color-panel">
          <span class="slider round"></span>
      </label>
  </div>
  ```
* **Behavior**:
  - On change:
    - If the user is authenticated and `has_premium === 1` in their user profile:
      - Swaps the background palette elements in `#game-toolbar .colors` with a secondary premium range of colors (e.g. pastel palettes, custom gradients, or full spectrum options).
    - If the user is **not** premium:
      - Automatically sets the toggle back to "off".
      - Redirects/prompts the player to the **Razorpay Upgrade screen** stating: *"Pay ₹25 to unlock premium colors for lifetime and remove ads for 6 months!"*

